HEADWORD: Snails
<hw>'Snails</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos> <def>God's nails, or
His nails, that is, the nails with which the Savior was fastened to the
cross; -- an ancient form of oath, corresponding to '<xex>Od's
bodikins</xex> (dim. of <xex>body</xex>, i.e., God's dear body).</def>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

